{Name}{}{Cristopher}
{DescAliveShort}{}{You see a saylor.}
{DescAliveFull}{}{Tough man with a weather-beaten skin.}
{Speech 1}{}{Pre-dialog settings}
{Speech 1 Answer 2}{}{First meeting - neutral.}
{Speech 1 Answer 25}{}{First meeting - high karma.}
{Speech 1 Answer 23}{}{Fully acquainted.}
{Speech 1 Answer 36}{}{Not quite acquainted}
{Speech 1 Answer 24}{}{Dislikes you.}
{Speech 1 Answer 35}{}{Irritated.}
{Speech 1 Answer 35*}{}{Irritated and about to get angry.}
{Speech 1 Answer 30}{}{Fell out.}
{Speech 1 Answer 26}{}{First meeting - low intelligence.}
{Speech 1 Answer 28}{}{Low intelligence - dislikes you.}
{Speech 1 Answer 29}{}{Low intelligence - irritated.}
{Speech 1 Answer 30*}{}{Low intelligence - made him angry.}
{Speech 2}{}{Hi there! I didn't expect to meet another sea traveler! Welcome aboard my vessel! My name is Cristopher.}
{Speech 2 Answer 3}{}{A vessel, huh? I thought you'd been shipwrecked.}
{Speech 2 Answer 4}{}{And I'm @pname@. Where are you headed, Cristopher?}
{Speech 2 Answer 30}{}{This is a robbery, bitch! Hand over everything you've got right now, or I'll gut your dog!}
{Speech 2 Answer 15}{}{This is a robbery, bitch! Hand over everything you've got right now, or I'll gut your dog!}
{Speech 2 Answer 5}{}{Hi, hi. My name is @pname@. But I really have to sail on now - I just stopped by to say hello.}
{Speech 2 Answer 5*}{}{Hi, thanks. But I'm already moving on - I just wanted to see what this contraption floating here was.}
{Speech 25}{}{Ooh, well now, if it isn't @pname@ in person! I've heard about you - they say you helped a lot of people on the mainland. Welcome aboard my vessel! My name is Cristopher.}
{Speech 25 Answer 3}{}{A vessel, huh? I thought you'd been shipwrecked.}
{Speech 25 Answer 4}{}{And I'm @pname@. Where are you headed, Cristopher?}
{Speech 25 Answer 30}{}{Yes, I'm @pname@, but on Sundays I'm a sea pirate. Hand over everything you've got right now, or I'll gut your dog!}
{Speech 25 Answer 15}{}{Yes, I'm @pname@, but on Sundays I'm a sea pirate. Hand over everything you've got right now, or I'll gut your dog!}
{Speech 25 Answer 5}{}{Hi, hi. Yes, that's me. But I really have to sail on now - I just stopped by to say hello.}
{Speech 25 Answer 5*}{}{Hi, thanks. But I'm already moving on - I just wanted to see what this contraption floating here was.}
{Speech 3}{}{Hey, don't you dare insult my tub, @sex@|pal|sister|! It's called a raft and it floats better than that rusty piece of junk of yours!}
{Speech 3 Answer 6}{}{Okay, okay, sorry. So where are you headed on this "raft" of yours?}
{Speech 3 Answer 4}{}{Hey, don't take it so seriously, I'm just joking. So, my name is @pname@. Where are you headed, Cristopher?}
{Speech 3 Answer 30}{}{Better or not, it's about to stop floating altogether if you don't hand over your money.}
{Speech 3 Answer 15}{}{Better or not, it's about to stop floating altogether if you don't hand over your money.}
{Speech 3 Answer 5}{}{Well, since you're not shipwrecked, there's nothing for me to do here, bye!}
{Speech 4}{}{Very nice, @pname@. It may be hard to believe, but I'm traveling all the way to Alaska itself! In case you don't know - it's very far to the north. There are almost no people there, and the sea is bound in ice.}
{Speech 4 Answer 7}{}{And what the hell dragged you all the way out there?}
{Speech 4 Answer 7*}{}{Oh, that's very interesting. And what goal are you pursuing, setting out on such a long journey?}
{Speech 4 Answer 31}{}{Ice, huh? Ice only happens in a fridge, you idiot! I'm getting off your boat, you're a nutcase, apparently.}
{Speech 4 Answer 5}{}{Very interesting, yes. But I have to go! Bye!}
{Speech 5}{}{Hey! Stop! Don't you know that all sea travelers are supposed to trade something with each other when they meet?}
{Speech 5 Answer Barter}{}{Well, let's see what you've got...}
{Speech 5 Answer 31}{}{I'm not interested.}
{Speech 5 Answer Barter*}{}{Show me your goods again, you've got some interesting little items there...}
{Speech 5 Answer 18}{}{Actually, I've changed my mind about leaving - I wanted to ask you about something...}
{Speech 5 Answer 37}{}{Well that's it, now I have to go.}
{Speech 6}{}{I can't tell things like that to a person whose name I don't even know!}
{Speech 6 Answer 4}{}{My name is @pname@.}
{Speech 6 Answer 4*}{}{Oh, I beg your pardon, where are my manners? My name is @pname@. Forgive me for not introducing myself right away.}
{Speech 6 Answer 31}{}{Like hell I'll tell you my name.}
{Speech 6 Answer 32}{}{I beg your pardon, but due to my convictions I cannot just reveal my name like that.}
{Speech 7}{}{Oh, it's a long story. Do you want to hear the whole thing?}
{Speech 7 Answer 9}{}{Go ahead.}
{Speech 7 Answer 8}{}{Nah, give me the short version.}
{Speech 8}{}{So, I picked up a radio signal from a settlement in Alaska. Turned out there are people living there too, and they have no mutations. Ever since then I've been sailing back and forth along the coast. I haul all sorts of junk from there, bring them plant seeds from here and other odds and ends.}
{Speech 8 Answer 9}{}{Oh, that's interesting. Let's hear the full story instead.}
{Speech 8 Answer 17}{}{Junk, you say? Can I buy something from you?}
{Speech 8 Answer Exit}{}{Cool. Well, all right, I have to go, it was interesting talking.}
{Speech 8 Answer 5}{}{Cool. Well, all right, I have to go, it was interesting talking.}
{Speech 9}{}{Let me start from the beginning. I was born in San Francisco, lived among fishermen, learned to tie tackle and watched the boats sail. Later I did odd jobs at Lou Chou's shop, fixing radios and all sorts of electronics.}
{Speech 9 Answer 10}{}{[Next]}
{Speech 9 Answer Exit}{}{Enough, I've changed my mind.}
{Speech 10}{}{So I had my own radio, you see. Sometimes I'd catch other people's chatter and listen to it while I worked, to make it less boring. And once I stumbled on someone's broadcast... They were saying: "Hello! This is Arcadia speaking! Come to us! We have food, and there are no mutations here!"}
{Speech 10 Answer 11}{}{[Next]}
{Speech 10 Answer Exit}{}{That's very interesting, but I have to go.}
{Speech 11}{}{That broadcast repeated every day... Turned out it was some city in Alaska where life had also survived. They told a lot of other interesting things, but my transmitter was too weak to answer them...}
{Speech 11 Answer 12}{}{[Next]}
{Speech 11 Answer Exit}{}{I don't have time to listen to fairy tales.}
{Speech 12}{}{And a dream was born in me: to set out for Arcadia. I'd already been out to sea with the fishermen and could cover a fairly long distance by boat along the coast. But I was afraid of depending on the wind and sailing under a sail, so I started building the "Enterprise." It's the raft you're standing on right now.}
{Speech 12 Answer 13}{}{[Next]}
{Speech 12 Answer Exit}{}{We're miles from shore right now. You've simply gotten lost at sea and you're raving. I don't feel safe on this raft, bye.}
{Speech 13}{}{And on the "Enterprise" I finally made it to Arcadia! The city really existed, and there were people there! They were descendants of the military who survived the missile strikes in a bunker. Food was actually pretty scarce for them, but the area around them was littered with tons of military junk from the Great War. Walk out into a field, dig a bit - and there's a sample of advanced weaponry the Brotherhood would tear your throat out for.}
{Speech 13 Answer 14}{}{[Next]}
{Speech 13 Answer Exit}{}{Now you're definitely lying. Bye, I don't want to listen to your fairy tales.}
{Speech 14}{}{The Arcadians supplied me with gifts, and I set off home. By selling their artifacts in San Francisco, I was able to equip a second expedition. Now I make regular trips to them. I haul plant seeds and other odds and ends there, and bring back pre-war technology. I've become one of the main weapon suppliers in San Francisco. I'm thinking about expanding the business.}
{Speech 14 Answer 17}{}{That's really cool. Can I buy something from you?}
{Speech 14 Answer 30}{}{Now hand over all your goods, please, unless you want me to blow up your little boat.}
{Speech 14 Answer 15}{}{Now hand over all your goods, please, unless you want me to blow up your little boat.}
{Speech 14 Answer 19}{}{Hmm. Won't you tell me where this Arcadia is?}
{Speech 14 Answer 5}{}{Thanks for the story, very interesting. Good luck with your voyages, I have to be on my way.}
{Speech 14 Answer 37}{}{Thanks for the story, very interesting. Good luck with your voyages, I have to be on my way.}
{Speech 15}{}{[The sailor stares at you in fear. You could swear you've never seen a man so frightened in your whole life.]}
{Speech 15 Answer 16}{}{Hey, what's the matter with you?}
{Speech 15 Answer 16*}{}{What, scared?!}
{Speech 15 Answer Exit}{}{[Attack]}
{Speech 15 Answer Exit*}{}{Hey, relax, I was joking.}
{Speech 16}{}{D-d-don't kill me, eh? See, I've spent most of the last three years far from California and never got the chance to sign up for that replication... These days people there aren't afraid to kill each other, but I'm scared of dying...}
{Speech 16 Answer Exit}{}{Wow. What luck, what luck. I've always dreamed of killing someone *for real*. [Attack]}
{Speech 16 Answer 34}{}{I need you, relax. Just hand over all your goods.}
{Speech 16 Answer Exit*}{}{Phew. Well, all right. Another time. Live for now, heh-heh.}
{Speech 17}{}{Here, take a look.@@Here's what I have for sale.@@Take a look, I've got some rare little items.@@You're in luck - I just happen to be hauling a shipment of goods from Arcadia.@@Take your pick. Exclusive.}
{Speech 17 Answer Barter}{}{[Barter]}
{Speech 17 Answer 18}{}{Listen, to hell with the goods, there's one question I'm interested in...}
{Speech 17 Answer Exit}{}{I've actually changed my mind about trading, I have to go. Good luck!}
{Speech 17 Answer Barter*}{}{Show me your goods again...}
{Speech 17 Answer Exit*}{}{That's all, thanks.}
{Speech 18}{}{What do you want to know?@@What are you interested in?@@Well, ask away.@@Ask your question, I'll help however I can.}
{Speech 18 Answer 19}{}{Will you share the coordinates of Arcadia?}
{Speech 18 Answer 22}{}{What are your plans for the future?}
{Speech 18 Answer 7}{}{Tell me again how you became a traveler.}
{Speech 18 Answer 39}{}{Nice dog you've got, Cristopher. Where did you get one like that?}
{Speech 18 Answer 17}{}{To hell with it, just show me the goods.}
{Speech 18 Answer Exit}{}{Actually, I don't need anything. Bye!}
{Speech 19}{}{Uhh, no. That's a trade secret! [Smiles] I'm thinking of eventually expanding my business, hiring workers. I wouldn't want competition. Nor pirates showing up, for that matter.}
{Speech 19 Answer 20}{}{But this is humanity's heritage! People should know that there are survivors somewhere else... We need to develop, to exchange knowledge.}
